abstract: TWENTY-TWO days almost to the hour after Tug McGraw was saluted in a downtown Philadelphia parade as a World Series folk  hero, he was snubbed in baseball's draft for its free-agent auction. Not merely insulted at being chosen by only a few teams in the late rounds, but ignored completely.
